# Build-context excludes. Without this, `COPY . .` shipped the HOST's 302MB of
# node_modules (built for Windows) into the image: pnpm then tried to wipe the
# incompatible modules dir and aborted for want of a TTY, so the image never
# built. Keep the context to sources + manifests; the image installs its own
# dependencies from the frozen lockfile.

# Dependencies — always reinstalled inside the image
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build output + caches
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
.turbo
**/.turbo
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo
coverage
**/coverage
.vite
**/.vite

# VCS + local tooling
.git
.github
.gitignore
.claude
.vscode
.idea

# Secrets and local env — must never enter an image layer
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
deploy/.env

# Test / dev artefacts
e2e
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
fixtures/out
**/.tmp-imports
deploy/backups

# Docs (not needed at runtime; keep images lean)
*.md
docs
!README.md
